{
  "texts": [
    "The two methods can be combined to achieve even greater savings, although some adaptation is required.",
    "VeLoRA (Miles et al., 2024) also aims to compress linear layer activations, however, they apply their paradigm to two specific layers of the model only, thus making their benefit marginal.",
    "We compare with their projection in our experimental section, see Section 5.",
    "In any case, both (Miles et al., 2024) and (Yang et al., 2024) remain unexplored for the setting of pretraining LLMs.",
    "Activation Checkpointing CKPT (Chen et al., 2016), also known as gradient checkpointing, reduces the memory footprint of the entire computation graph by saving the activations only at specific layers, or checkpoints."
  ]
}